=====================<br>I need to petition for what happened on Antonious Bayle server Friday February 15th 2002 around 8.00 pm GMT.<br>Pretorians have been present in Skyfire for 26 hours in a row when finally Zordak Ragefire spawns.<br>One of our enchanter mezz him to give us the chance to finish few other roamers , a Guardian Wurm included. Ariella states she will not respect the fact we agroed the mob first because she has been waiting too long, as you can read in Sayeh report/petition. Suddendly Zordak’s mez is broken and run outside the camp like someone pulled him, sorry i don’t have any proof of it but i had the strong feeling someone tried to get his “attention”. We weren’t ready and had anyway to kill Zordak and trigger the dragon Zordaricous. We got a wipe out but we were ready after a bit while to kill him.<br>Tuleno agroed him with snare and was coming straight towards our camp when i receive a tell from GM Sefyte. I told him that we are ready to kill him again and that my petition was just a caution against possible kill stealing. I consider the topic closed but after a while (Tuleno died , dressed up without a rez and went back to get the mob), i receive a tell from Sefyte that a mob kited is not considered engaged…<br>????<br>First time a GM feels the need to address me without any request.<br>I had to reply to him that this was really different from what has been always stated by GMs specially on Quellious.<br>As you can read in my /report Sefyte, he has been stating that final ruling is that kiting a mob not on the purpose to kill it is not considered mob engagement….<br>Ok, ok.<br>Then rules have been changed! Cool! <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Now someone explain to me why a GM assumes we were not going to kill him</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. We were just waiting for dragon to be pulled to camp. We were ready to kill it and X‘Agon still had only 1 group when i received the odd tell from Sefyte.<br>I am not discussing Sefyte acts. But you need to restore the whole thing. Now Lenor from X‘Agon has an epic piece which Sayeh should have had, as the dragon was being pulled to camp when intercepted from X‘Agon. Maybe my understanding of &quot;kiting&quot; is wrong and i will stop using this term. The mob was snared and escorted where we all were waiting. And you need to restore it for 2 reasons. Because Pretorians have been Ksed even with GM consent based on a wrong assumption. And because you don’t want EQ to fall into Chaos. Can you imagine? Someone in Karnors Castle snares Captain and another group can intercept the pull? How many zones and how many mobs are in EQ? Do you really want to have billions of petitions per day?<br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> If I take literally the words from GM Sefyte</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> we have been KSed, as it was not the case he assumed to be, we were not taking the dragon around the zone, but to the spot we (around 30 full buffed and rdy to action people) chose to kill him, WITH THE PURPOSE TO KILL IT, when X‘Agon interferred.<br>Please restore.<br>Another topic, even if I think that my petition is already supported by effective arguments.<br>What is the purpose in having first Zordak Ragefire and then the dragon? No loot from Zordak, Sayeh has got only a plasmatic robe from him, all the loot are on dragon. Isn’t to set a priority on kill? Pretorians triggered the dragon by killing the KoS Zordak. Ok we failed on first but we were ready to kill him again when X’Agon was still porting people to Skyfire, I repeat only 1 group from that guild was present in zone when Tuleno snared him on the purpose to take him to camp. I suggest a revision of the quest, no point in having 2 mob and then 2 items dropping only from the second. You would avoid guild wars by giving a loot each. So noone would think of Ksing the dragon once triggered. At the moment the only reason for 2 mob is just because agroing the first you get the right to kill the second, IMHO.<br><br>Gardile, lvl 60 Druid<br>Sayeh lvl 56 Cleric<br>Leader of Pretorians<br>Antonious Bayle<br>======================================<br>Yeah i am really unhappy, specially because a GM was there and took a decision based on a wrong assumption. But i need to add that i really disapprove X'Agon acts.<br>To be respected need to respect others first.<br>I feel proud to say that we decided to give up with RF on Thursday February 14th at 2 pm GMT, after we realized that X'Agon and Magus Amicitia were already there. We went back to get rdy to kill RF only few hours later, after both guilds left the zone.<br>We will go on with our policy and keep paying respect to other Guilds, but i am afraid, X'Agon lost its chance to be respected from us.<br><br>Gardile<br><br> <p></p><span class=m><i></i></span><hr size=1>   &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=http://pub44.ezboard.com/fantoniusbaylecommunitycentrefrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=198.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/reply.gif border=0 width=20 height=20 alt="reply to this message" align=absmiddle></a>   <br><br></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td colspan=2><table cellpadding=8 cellspacing=0 width=100%><tr><td nowrap width=20% valign=top><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub44.ezboard.com/ufeeldary.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Feeldary</A> </span><br><BR><img src=http://www.multimania.com/feeldary/avanov.jpg length=152 height=200><br> <span class=usertitle>Gnoll Commander</span><br>  Posts: <b>19</b><br></td><td valign=top align=left class=m width=80%><span class=m><font color=#6699F>Posted: 2/16/02 1:58:35 am</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br><span class=title> Re: When a GM assumes...</span><hr size=1> gms suck nuff'said <p><center><img src="http://www.multimania.com/feeldary/feelsig.jpg"><BR><img src="http://www.multimania.com/feeldary/sig/critical2.gif"><BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=11040">Magelo</A></center></p>