g with Mobs of a certain spawntime/ level/ encounter  without higher admitance. <br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  GMs </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Level 56 to 59 (Could be 60. They changed this too.)<br>They have access to all GM items and Commands. They can bann players, kick players, suspend players, change names etc. The can enter any zone. They *can* interfere with allmost any Mob in Game. (Still a GM would never /kill Vulak for example.) They are Verant emplyoes and Paid for their time.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Lead GMs </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br><br>Level 60. All listed at GMs + the power to withdraw all others Decisions. Basicaly the boss of the server. They are the law.<br><br>Knowing this, Apprentice Guides and Guides can be very unfamiliar with the game in generall. Its possible to get a GM to a zone like skyfire and get one that enters the zone for the first time. Also, about 95% of the situations a Guide is called to help are not covered by the PnP policis (or the policis are not usable there). That means the decision is just about common sense. And thats a very rare gift among GMs. As it turns out, customer service is okay when it comes to bugs and such, but social problems like 2 racing Guilds rarely have something to do with justice. Most with whom sounds more beliveable.  <p>------------------------------------------------------------<Font size="-2"><BR><I> The sun is sleeping quietly, once upon a century, <BR> Wistful oceans calm and red, Ardent caresses laid to rest, <BR> For my dreams I hold my life, for wishes I behold my night<BR>The truth at the end of time, losing faith makes a crime<BR><BR>I wish for this night-time, to last for a lifetime <BR>The darkness around me, Shores of a solar sea<BR>Oh how I wish to go down with the sun<BR>Sleeping, Weeping, With you...<BR><BR>Sorrow has a human heart, from my god it will depart<BR>I'd sail before a thousand moons, never finding where to go<BR>Two hundred twenty-two days 